result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Suzzette L. Burnett

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Suzzette L. Burnett in court.  Attorney Michael C Turner in court for Suzzette L. Burnett.  Prosecuting attorney Jordan W. Feest in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
State moves to dismiss and read in this file as part of a plea agreement with 21CF990, 21CF989, 21CF894, 22CF483 and 22CF491.  Motion granted.

BAIL MODIFICATION:  Defendant is wishing to have the no contact provision modified from no contact to no assaultive contact with J.B. in 21CF894, 21CF419, 22CF190 and 21CF990.  The Court is taking the position that case nos. 22CF483 and 22CF491 are a result of Defendant violating the no contact provision.  Court therefore denies the modification at this time until further documentation is provided that the modification request is mutual.  Defense counsel will continue to secure such documentation.  Attorney Feest to prepare order. 
Additionally, Defendant wishes to have the cash bail converted to signature bond in 22CF491.   Counsel makes argument for a reduction or conversion of the cash bond.  State is objecting to a reduction based on past performance while on bond and feels that the current cash bail is appropriate.  Court finds that a reduction of the $500.00 cash bail is not appropriate at this time.  Attorney Feest to prepare order. 
Scheduling conference scheduled for September 30, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

2:38 PM Defendant Suzzette L. Burnett appeared by video.  Attorneys Jacalyn Labre and Marconi DeFranca Barros appear for Jordan W. Feest by video for State of Wisconsin.  Michael C Turner appeared by video for Suzzette L. Burnett. Inducement made.  
Defendant waives her right to a preliminary hearing.  Defendant is bound over to Circuit Court Branch 1 for further proceedings.
ARRAIGNMENT
Information filed.  Not guilty plea(s).  Jury Calendar.  Offer deadline is set for August 19, 2022.  
Minutes.

records.descr: Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant

records.addlTxt: Defendant's Motion for Discovery and Inspection
Order to report to MTPD for photo and prints

BAIL HEARING - 
Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crime of 5 cts. felony bail jumping.  The matter is continued for initial appearance on 07-11-22 at 1:30 p.m.  Bail is set at $5,000.00 recognizance bond with the conditions that he report to the Manitowoc City Police Department for fingerprints, photographs and identifying information within 48 hours or, if incarcerated, within 72 hours of release and defendant is to have no contact with Justin Burnett and no contact with the premises at 1029 S. 14th Street, Manitowoc, WI.   The court will allow a one-time contact with the residence, with the aid of law enforcement, after the 72 hour no contact provision has expired, to obtain personal belongings.   Bail furnished and defendant is released from custody.
Minutes.
